cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on developing a new approach for regularization of features in reinforcement learning (RL) and demonstrating its effectiveness in several test environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is concerned with the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. 

The paper also involves the use of deep RL and Atari 2600 games, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper involves optimization and convergence analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories.
